#. <html><head><meta charset="UTF-8"><meta author="Bhikkhu Brahmali"><meta content="Pali text from the Mahāsaṅgīti Tipiṭaka Buddhavasse 2500" name="description"><title></title></head><body><div id="text" lang="en"><section class="sutta" id="pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr "Theravāda Collection on Monastic Law"

#. </p><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr "Monks’ rules and their analysis"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs0.3"
msgid "Saṃ­ghā­di­sesa­kaṇḍa"
msgstr "Monks’ Suspension"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs0.4"
msgid "Dubba­ca­sikkhā­pada"
msgstr "12. The training rule on being difficult to correct"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.309"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.12.1"></a></p><p><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1729"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā kosambiyaṃ viharati ghositārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Kosambī in Ghosita’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā channo anācāraṃ ācarati."
msgstr "At that time Venerable Channa was behaving improperly."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs1.3"
msgid "Bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr "The monks would tell him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs1.4"
msgid "“māvuso channa, evarūpaṃ akāsi."
msgstr "“Don’t do that;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs1.5"
msgid "Netaṃ kappatī”ti."
msgstr "it’s not allowable,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs1.6"
msgid "So evaṃ vadeti—"
msgstr "and he would reply,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs1.7"
msgid "“kiṃ nu kho nāma tumhe, āvuso, maṃ vattabbaṃ maññatha?"
msgstr "“Who are you to correct me?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs1.8"
msgid "Ahaṃ kho nāma tumhe vadeyyaṃ."
msgstr "I should correct you!"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs1.9"
msgid "Amhākaṃ buddho amhākaṃ dhammo"
msgstr "The Buddha is mine; the Teaching is mine."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs1.10"
msgid "amhākaṃ ayyaputtena dhammo abhisamito."
msgstr "The Master realized the Truth because of me."

#. VAR: ussāreyya → ussādeyya (bj, s1-3)
#. VAR: tiṇakaṭ­ṭha­paṇṇa­sa­ṭaṃ → tiṇakaṭ­ṭhapaṇṇa­ka­saṭaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs1.11"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi nāma mahāvāto vāyanto tiṇakaṭ­ṭha­paṇṇa­sa­ṭaṃ ekato ussāreyya, "
"seyyathā vā pana nadī pabbateyyā saṅ­kha­se­vālapa­ṇa­kaṃ ekato ussāreyya;"
msgstr ""
"Just as a great wind lifts up grass, sticks, and fallen leaves all at once, "
"just as a mountain stream lifts up the leaves of various water plants all at "
"once,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs1.12"
msgid ""
"evameva tumhe nānānāmā nānāgottā nānājaccā nānākulā pabbajitā ekato ussāritā."
msgstr ""
"so too you–having various names, various families, various castes, various "
"clans–having gone forth, have been lifted up together."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs1.13"
msgid "Kiṃ nu kho nāma tumhe, āvuso, maṃ vattabbaṃ maññatha?"
msgstr "So, who are you to correct me?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs1.14"
msgid "Ahaṃ kho nāma tumhe vadeyyaṃ."
msgstr "I should correct you!"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs1.15"
msgid "Amhākaṃ buddho amhākaṃ dhammo"
msgstr "The Buddha is mine; the Teaching is mine."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs1.16"
msgid "amhākaṃ ayyaputtena dhammo abhisamito”ti."
msgstr "The Master realized the Truth because of me.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs1.17"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs1.18"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized him,"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.310"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs1.19"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma āyasmā channo bhikkhūhi sahadhammikaṃ vuccamāno attānaṃ "
"avacanīyaṃ karissatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“How can Venerable Channa make himself incorrigible when he’s legitimately "
"corrected by the monks?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.178"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1730"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs1.20"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ channaṃ aneka­pariyā­yena vigarahitvā "
"bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "They rebuked Venerable Channa in many ways and then told the Master. …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs1.21"
msgid ""
"“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, channa, bhikkhūhi sahadhammikaṃ vuccamāno attānaṃ "
"avacanīyaṃ karosī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"He said, “Is it true, Channa, that you make yourself incorrigible when you "
"are legitimately corrected by the monks?"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs1.22"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs1.23"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs1.24"
msgid ""
"kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, bhikkhūhi sahadhammikaṃ vuccamāno attānaṃ "
"avacanīyaṃ karissasi."
msgstr "Foolish man, how can you act like this?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs1.25"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs1.26"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs1.26a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs1.27"
msgid ""
"“Bhikkhu paneva dubbacajātiko hoti uddesa­pariyā­pan­nesu sikkhāpadesu "
"bhikkhūhi sahadhammikaṃ vuccamāno attānaṃ avacanīyaṃ karoti—"
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk is difficult to correct, and he makes himself incorrigible when "
"he is legitimately corrected by the monks concerning the training rules that "
"are recited, saying,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs1.28"
msgid ""
"‘mā maṃ āyasmanto kiñci avacuttha kalyāṇaṃ vā pāpakaṃ vā, ahampāyasmante na "
"kiñci vakkhāmi kalyāṇaṃ vā pāpakaṃ vā,"
msgstr ""
"“Venerables, don’t say anything to me, either positive or negative, and I "
"won’t say anything to you, either positive or negative;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs1.29"
msgid "vira­ma­thā­yasmanto mama vacanāyā’ti,"
msgstr "please refrain from correcting me,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs1.30"
msgid "so bhikkhu bhikkhūhi evamassa vacanīyo—"
msgstr "then the monks should correct him in this way:"

#. VAR: vacanīya­mevā­yasmā → vacanīyameva āyasmā (s1-3) | vacanīyaṃ eva āyasmā (pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs1.31"
msgid "‘māyasmā attānaṃ avacanīyaṃ akāsi, vacanīya­mevā­yasmā attānaṃ karotu,"
msgstr "“Venerable, be easy to correct, not incorrigible."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.311"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs1.32"
msgid ""
"āyasmāpi bhikkhū vadetu sahadhammena, bhikkhūpi āyasmantaṃ vakkhanti "
"sahadhammena."
msgstr ""
"And please give legitimate correction to the monks, and the monks will do "
"the same to you."

#. VAR: saṃvaddhā → saṃvaḍḍhā (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs1.33"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ saṃvaddhā hi tassa bhagavato parisā yadidaṃ añña­mañña­vaca­nena "
"añña­mañña­vuṭṭhā­panenā’ti."
msgstr ""
"For it’s in this way that the Master’s community has grown, that is, through "
"mutual correction and mutual rehabilitation.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs1.34"
msgid ""
"Evañca so bhikkhu bhikkhūhi vuccamāno tatheva paggaṇheyya, so bhikkhu "
"bhikkhūhi yāvatatiyaṃ sama­nubhā­si­tabbo tassa paṭinissaggāya."
msgstr ""
"If that monk still continues as before, the monks should admonish him up to "
"three times to make him stop."

#. VAR: sama­nubhā­si­yamāno → sama­nubhā­si­yamāno (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs1.35"
msgid ""
"Yāvatatiyañce sama­nubhā­si­yamāno taṃ paṭi­nissaj­jeyya, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ;"
msgstr "If he then stops, that is good."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs1.36"
msgid "no ce paṭi­nissaj­jeyya, saṃghādiseso”ti."
msgstr "If not, he commits an offense entailing suspension.’”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs1.37"
msgid "(<em>12</em>:<strong>16</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.12.2"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1732"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.1"
msgid "Bhikkhū paneva dubbacajātiko hotīti"
msgstr "If a monk is difficult to correct:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.2"
msgid ""
"dubbaco hoti dova­cassaka­raṇehi dhammehi samannāgato akkhamo "
"appa­dak­khi­ṇag­gāhī anusāsaniṃ."
msgstr ""
"if he is difficult to correct, endowed with qualities that make him hard to "
"correct, resistant, not receiving instructions respectfully."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1733"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.3"
msgid "Uddesa­pariyā­pan­nesu sikkhāpadesūti"
msgstr "Concerning the training rules that are recited:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.4"
msgid "pāti­mokkha­pariyā­pan­nesu sikkhāpadesu."
msgstr "concerning the training rules of the monastic code."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1734"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.5"
msgid "Bhikkhūhīti"
msgstr "The monks:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.6"
msgid "aññehi bhikkhūhi."
msgstr "other monks."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1735"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.7"
msgid "Sahadhammikaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Legitimately:"

#. </span></p><div class="gloss"><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.8"
msgid "yaṃ bhagavatā paññattaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ,"
msgstr "about whatever training rule has been laid down by the Master—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.9"
msgid "etaṃ sahadhammikaṃ nāma."
msgstr "this is called “legitimately.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1736"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.312"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.10"
msgid "Tena vuccamāno attānaṃ avacanīyaṃ karoti—"
msgstr ""
"When he is corrected concerning that, he makes himself incorrigible, saying,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.11"
msgid ""
"“mā maṃ āyasmanto kiñci avacuttha kalyāṇaṃ vā pāpakaṃ vā, ahampāyasmante na "
"kiñci vakkhāmi kalyāṇaṃ vā pāpakaṃ vā."
msgstr ""
"“Venerables, don’t say anything to me, either positive or negative, and I "
"won’t say anything to you, either positive or negative;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.12"
msgid "Vira­ma­thā­yasmanto mama vacanāyā”ti."
msgstr "please refrain from correcting me.”"

#. </p></div><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1737"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.13"
msgid "So bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Him:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.14"
msgid "yo so dubbacajātiko bhikkhu."
msgstr "the monk who is difficult to correct."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.179"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1738"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.15"
msgid "Bhikkhūhīti"
msgstr "The monks:"

#. </span></p><div class="gloss"><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.16"
msgid "aññehi bhikkhūhi."
msgstr "Other monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.17"
msgid "Ye passanti ye suṇanti tehi vattabbo—"
msgstr "those who see it or hear about it. They should say,"

#. <span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.18"
msgid "“māyasmā attānaṃ avacanīyaṃ akāsi."
msgstr "“Venerable, be easy to correct,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.19"
msgid "Vacanīyameva āyasmā attānaṃ karotu."
msgstr "not incorrigible."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.20"
msgid ""
"Āyasmāpi bhikkhū vadetu sahadhammena, bhikkhūpi āyasmantaṃ vakkhanti "
"sahadhammena."
msgstr ""
"And please give legitimate correction to the monks, and the monks will do "
"the same to you."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.21"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ saṃvaddhā hi tassa bhagavato parisā yadidaṃ añña­mañña­vaca­nena "
"añña­mañña­vuṭṭhā­panenā”ti."
msgstr ""
"For it’s in this way that the Master’s community has grown, that is, through "
"mutual correction and mutual rehabilitation.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.22"
msgid "Dutiyampi vattabbo."
msgstr "And they should say this a second"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.23"
msgid "Tatiyampi vattabbo."
msgstr "and a third time."

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.24"
msgid "Sace paṭinissajjati, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ;"
msgstr "If he stops, that is good."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.25"
msgid "no ce paṭinissajjati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he does not stop, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. <span class="subrule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.26"
msgid "Sutvā na vadanti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If those who hear about it do not say anything, they commit an offense of "
"wrong conduct."

#. </span>
#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.27"
msgid "So bhikkhu saṃgha­majjhampi ākaḍḍhitvā vattabbo—"
msgstr ""
"That monk, even if he has to be dragged into the middle of the Order, should "
"be spoken to thus:"

#. <span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.28"
msgid "“māyasmā attānaṃ avacanīyaṃ akāsi … pe …"
msgstr ""
"“Venerable, be easy to correct, not incorrigible. And please give legitimate "
"correction to the monks, and the monks will do the same to you. For it’s in "
"this way that the Master’s community has grown, that is, through mutual "
"correction"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.29"
msgid "añña­mañña­vuṭṭhā­panenā”ti."
msgstr "and mutual rehabilitation.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.30"
msgid "Dutiyampi vattabbo."
msgstr "They should say this a second"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.31"
msgid "Tatiyampi vattabbo."
msgstr "and a third time."

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.32"
msgid "Sace paṭinissajjati, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ;"
msgstr "If he stops, that is good."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.33"
msgid "no ce paṭinissajjati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he does not stop, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p></div><p><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.34"
msgid "So bhikkhu sama­nubhā­si­tabbo."
msgstr "Should admonish him:"

#. </span></p><div class="gloss"><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.35"
msgid "“Evañca pana, bhikkhave, sama­nubhā­si­tabbo."
msgstr "“And, monks, he should be admonished in this way."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.36"
msgid "Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṃgho ñāpetabbo—"
msgstr "A competent and capable monk should inform the Order:"

#. </p><div class="kamma"><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1739"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.37"
msgid "‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṃgho."
msgstr "‘Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.38"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu bhikkhūhi sahadhammikaṃ vuccamāno attānaṃ avacanīyaṃ "
"karoti."
msgstr ""
"This monk so-and-so makes himself incorrigible when he’s legitimately "
"corrected by the monks."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.39"
msgid "So taṃ vatthuṃ na paṭinissajjati."
msgstr "He keeps on doing it."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.40"
msgid ""
"Yadi saṃghassa pattakallaṃ, saṃgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuṃ samanubhāseyya tassa "
"vatthussa paṭinissaggāya."
msgstr ""
"If it seems appropriate to the Order, the Order should admonish him to make "
"him stop."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.41"
msgid "Esā ñatti."
msgstr "This is the motion."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1740"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.42"
msgid "Suṇātu me, bhante, saṃgho."
msgstr "Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.43"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu bhikkhūhi sahadhammikaṃ vuccamāno attānaṃ avacanīyaṃ "
"karoti."
msgstr ""
"This monk so-and-so makes himself incorrigible when he’s legitimately "
"corrected by the monks."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.44"
msgid "So taṃ vatthuṃ na paṭinissajjati."
msgstr "He keeps on doing it."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.45"
msgid ""
"Saṃgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuṃ samanubhāsati tassa vatthussa paṭinissaggāya."
msgstr "The Order admonishes him to make him stop."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.46"
msgid ""
"Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa bhikkhuno samanubhāsanā tassa vatthussa "
"paṭinissaggāya, so tuṇhassa;"
msgstr ""
"Any monk who approves of admonishing him to make him stop should remain "
"silent."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.47"
msgid "yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya."
msgstr "Any monk who does not approve should say so."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1741"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.48"
msgid "Dutiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi … pe …"
msgstr "A second time …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.49"
msgid "tatiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi—"
msgstr "A third time I speak on this matter:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.50"
msgid "suṇātu me, bhante, saṃgho."
msgstr "Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.51"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu bhikkhūhi sahadhammikaṃ vuccamāno attānaṃ avacanīyaṃ "
"karoti."
msgstr ""
"This monk so-and-so makes himself incorrigible when he’s legitimately "
"corrected by the monks."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.52"
msgid "So taṃ vatthuṃ na paṭinissajjati."
msgstr "He keeps on doing it."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.53"
msgid ""
"Saṃgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuṃ samanubhāsati tassa vatthussa paṭinissaggāya."
msgstr "The Order admonishes him to make him stop."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.54"
msgid ""
"Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa bhikkhuno samanubhāsanā tassa vatthussa "
"paṭinissaggāya, so tuṇhassa;"
msgstr ""
"Any monk who approves of admonishing him to make him stop should remain "
"silent."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.55"
msgid "yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya."
msgstr "Any monk who does not approve should say so."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1742"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.56"
msgid ""
"Samanubhaṭṭho saṃghena itthannāmo bhikkhu tassa vatthussa paṭinissaggāya."
msgstr "This monk so-and-so has been admonished by the Order to make him stop."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.57"
msgid "Khamati saṃghassa, tasmā tuṇhī,"
msgstr "The Order approves and is therefore silent."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.58"
msgid "evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti."
msgstr "I will remember it thus.’”"

#. </p></div></div><hr><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1743"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.59"
msgid "Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ,"
msgstr "After the motion, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.60"
msgid "dvīhi kammavācāhi thullaccayā,"
msgstr ""
"After each of the first two announcements, he commits a serious offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.61"
msgid "kamma­vācā­pari­yosāne āpatti saṃ­ghā­di­sesassa."
msgstr ""
"When the last announcement is finished, he commits an offense entailing "
"suspension."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.313"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.62"
msgid ""
"Saṃghādisesaṃ ajjhā­pajjan­tassa ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ, dvīhi kammavācāhi "
"thullaccayā paṭippas­sam­bhanti."
msgstr ""
"For one who commits the offense entailing suspension, the offense of wrong "
"conduct and the serious offenses are annulled."

#. </p><hr><p><a class="sc" id="16"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1744"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.63"
msgid "Saṃghādisesoti"
msgstr "He commits an offense entailing suspension:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs2.64"
msgid "… pe … tenapi vuccati “saṃghādiseso”ti."
msgstr "… Therefore, too, it is called “an offense entailing suspension.”"

#. </span>
#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs3.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="17"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-ss.12.3"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.12.3.1"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1745"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs3.1.1"
msgid ""
"Dhammakamme dhamma­kamma­saññī na paṭinissajjati, āpatti saṃ­ghā­di­sesassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is a legitimate procedure, and he perceives it as legitimate, but he "
"does not stop, he commits an offense entailing suspension."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="18"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1746"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs3.1.2"
msgid "Dhammakamme vematiko na paṭinissajjati, āpatti saṃ­ghā­di­sesassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is a legitimate procedure, but he is unsure if it is, and he does not "
"stop, he commits an offense entailing suspension."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="19"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1747"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs3.1.3"
msgid ""
"Dhammakamme adhamma­kamma­saññī na paṭinissajjati, āpatti saṃ­ghā­di­sesassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is a legitimate procedure, but he perceives it as illegitimate, and he "
"does not stop, he commits an offense entailing suspension."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="20"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1748"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs3.1.4"
msgid "Adhammakamme dhamma­kamma­saññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is an illegitimate procedure, but he perceives it as legitimate, he "
"commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="21"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1749"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs3.1.5"
msgid "Adhammakamme vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is an illegitimate procedure, but he is unsure if it is, he commits an "
"offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="22"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1750"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs3.1.6"
msgid "Adhammakamme adhamma­kamma­saññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is an illegitimate procedure, and he perceives it as illegitimate, he "
"commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs3.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="23"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.12.3.2"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1751"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs3.2.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs3.2.2"
msgid "asama­nu­bhāsan­tassa,"
msgstr "if he has not been admonished;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs3.2.3"
msgid "paṭi­nissaj­jan­tassa,"
msgstr "if he stops;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs3.2.4"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs3.2.5"
msgid "ādi­kammi­kas­sāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="24"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1752"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss12:pts-cs3.2.6"
msgid "Dubba­ca­sikkhā­padaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dvādasamaṃ."
msgstr ""
"The twelfth rule, training rule on being difficult to correct, is finished."

